caption: Very busy location. Was looking for a vegan dish and when googled this place popped up. I ordered the bbq shrimp and cauliflower grits (not vegan) and my friend ordered the Pacific rim salmon with steamed vegetables and sweet potatoes. The total with 2 can teas was $33.63. I tasted  the salmon and it was very bland and taste boiled, but the veggies were ok (no seasoning) and the sweet potatoes were good. My dish took some getting used to. Taste more like Mediterranean food. The bbq definitely did not taste like bbq sauce.  The shrimp were not too rubbery. The cauliflower grits were a bit watery but were really good. The sauce is spicy but not overbearing. The tea taste more like pine tea and airfreshner. I would definitely recommend the salads and pizzas. Love the outdoor seating with spring air and covid free. Staff was friendly. Bathrooms clean. Indoor seating as well.
Too much seasoning and not a consistent temperature on the food.
Wish they had freshly sweet tea

I actually like that place, but my last order from them was totally messed up. Ordered an Asian Tuna salad, missed the mango, missed the almonds and the dressing was not the asian dressing they were saying, it was balsamic vinegar. I was disappointed this time
The food was light but very satisfying. The flavors were amazing. Very delicious food but not extremely expensive. I'll be coming back for sure!

I first tried Swegs when I worked at Ochsner Main Campus. Today I decided to try it again as I remember it being pretty good. Today I attempted to call in my order but to no avail. I called twice. I was put in hold both times and I wasn't able to place my order. I was hung up on after holding for a few minutes on the first try. Second attempt after being put on hold again, I held on for 5 minutes and decided to just go to the store to place my order. I had the 'bowl' if Turkey chili (it was more like a cup) for $5.95 and I ordered the buffalo chicken wrap for my mother. She enjoyed her wrap and the chili was very good. I will pay another visit soon! Hopefully next time someone will be able to take my order ahead of time.

Ordered a turkey burger and had it delivered by Uber Eats. Turkey burger was not fully cooked. I called and Eric advised that he'd make another one and I could come pick it up. Obviously I couldn't pick it up, that's why I ordered it to be delivered. As I expressed this to Eric, he proceeds to tell me that I have to contact Uber Eats, that he has nothing to do with the way it was delivered.(??) Uber Eats had nothing to do with the burger being under cooked. I asked if he would have another one delivered and he refused, said he was too busy and hung up!! Did this really just happen?? WOW, JUST WOW!!!!
The food is absolutely amazing. And also really healthy! They range from very healthy to sensible to a little indulgent but never too much.
Good food
Excellent options if you have dietary restrictions and my husband, who can eat anything, also loved it!  You must try the brownies, they are AMAZING!
Really glad that I discovered this place. Lots of healthy and quick lunch options & very good customer service (which is hard to find these days)
Definitely enjoy the comfort food and friendly service! Easy grab and go healthy choices that are SOO delicious.

This place has great food!  My girlfriend loves the Sirloin bleu cheese wedge salad;  both the crumbles and the dressing are delicious. The Turkey black bean chili has awesome flavor. I had the Mediterranean shrimp bowl last night and had them throw in some red pepper flakes for me which just made it that much better:  shrimp, kalamata olives, cucumbers, roasted bell peppers and a little pesto on top. Phenomenal!! The prices are really good for the portions.  Also got a sample of the BBQ shrimp and cauliflower grits. Can't wait to try more dishes.
Healthy, fast, and extremely friendly staff! The portions were also huge.
A healthier alternative for fast food. I am a picky eater so it's hard to eat healthy at lunch. SWEGS has options that I enjoy.
Great fresh food. Would go sgain.
Excellent value. Our favorites are the Turkey Burger and Tuna sliders. Ceaser salad is delicious.
Good food nice friendly service. Nice generous portions of healthy tasty food
Really good service, clean eating too! FYI their portabella panini sandwich didn't stand a chance once in my hands 🤣😋🤤🥪
Delicious. So delicious you might doubt the nutritional information. If swegs was closer to me I’d eat there 5 times a week instead of fast food.
Everything is made from the freshest ingredients.  Always delicious and healthy choices on the menu.  Always ask about the soup of the day.
Great food! The pre-packaged meals are perfect for week-night dinners.
Good healthy food
Good customer service. They give you the ability to order meals that are pre-made so you can have healthy meals throughout the week when you may be unable to make it in.

Everything is fresh and delicious.  The tuna sliders are fantastic, the cauliflower pizza crust is the best I've ever had, the turkey black bean chili hits the spot every time.  Yesterday I had my first swegg's turkey burger and it's been on my mind all day.  This place is decadence without guilt.
Really enjoyed the lunch options there, great  alternative to subways for a healthy meal.
Fresh, healthy food for dine in or to go. Always such great options. The pre-packaged meals are also great because they are portioned perfectly for a light but good meal.

All of the food comes from frozen bags that they just defrost. Your best bet is something fresh like a salad. They lock the door 15 mins early even though their time says they close at 9. You CAN NOT base your diet off of this food because they dont follow recipes. A steak will be one way today and a totally different way tomorrow. They are ALWAYS out of something also!  Horrible management, mistakes like this come directly from the top. This place was a big let down.

Awesome! Super healthy lunchbreak stop without sacrificing all the flavor. Love the meatballs and zoodles. No, it's not the same as spaghetti and meatballs but coming in at ~250 calories this dish is excellent.
Great healthy food with low price

They partner with Waitr but don’t have their full menu up. Every time I try to order they say they’ll fix it but no change happened. I made and order and spoke with a team member 3 times ensuring that it would be ready in time. It was not. It sat in the cue for over an hour. I cancelled though waitr because their  time wasn’t accurate either and she told me to come and it wasn’t even ready when I got there. I had to wait and no one would tell me when the food would be ready. I bring the food back to the office and two People’s orders are wrong. Not happy.
Really good. The pizza with cauliflower crust is excellent.
I am not impressed
Great advice from the friendly staff, and the food was YUMMY
The day shift always prepares excellent food!! Evening and weekend shift needs a little help.
Great food
good stuff
Good so delicious you forget it's so healthy!
Awesome food, the Southwest Chicken sliders are da bomb. Little pricey but worth it

Unfortunately, there have a few vegetarian options. However, you could still get a decent soup an salad in a nice ambience. We asked about our vegetarian choices and learned most of everything, contain some animal product. The girl at the register wasn't sure. -We don't have too many options- she said, pointing her finger at the  wall menu, explaining that few of the items did have the vegan colored icon.The place look nice, very clean and comfortable. If you are a meat eater, you'll probably love the healthy choices. We only wish they had more vegetarian options.
Healthy and delicious!
I got the turkey meatballs over zoodles & added a side of roasted sweet potatoes... sooooo good! The meatballs were seasoned well. Definitely enjoyed my meal!
Good healthy food! 1 L❤️ve

The restaurant is very clean with a a lot of natural light. We ordered the Mediterranean Shrimp salad and cauliflower shrimp and grits. The salad was extremely fresh and had a good amount of shrimp. The shrimp and grits was very flavorful and came out at a good temperature. The order came up pretty quickly and the cashier was polite. We walked over grabbed a daiquiri afterward. Overall it was a great experience and welcomed change from the standard fast-casual options. We left full and happy. I recommend anyone to stop in and try it out.
It was ok didnt like the service
Lovely decor and good, healthy food. The person at the counter could have been friendlier and more knowledgeable about the menu.

The Caesar salad I order was absolutely terrible. Parts of the lettuce had liquified, due to their old age. The lettuce was literally melting due to decomposition. The croutons were also partiality liquified as they were obviously sitting upon the decomposing salad absorbing their lettuce juice.  The salad used in my buffalo chicken sandwich I ordered was previously the meal of a very hungry insect. The leaves contained several holes throughout which more closely resembled Swiss cheese than lettuce.  My pregnant wife wanted a heathy option for lunch, instead we threw the lunch away and will avoid the restaurant going forward.
Great service. Great eats.
Atmosphere was cool.  Service was quick with only one person behind the counter.  Food was okay. Healthy choices though so I will be back
Great place
Turkey Meatballs and Zoodles; YUMMY!!!
Employees are rude, lock doors 15 minutes early, etc.  I rather spend money elsewhere.
Nice atmosphere Real good healthy food if you are into that
Amazing food and great customer service
My favorite is the Mediterranean shrimp bowl.  Great food & service

Healthy vegetarian friendly meals and great location! Great for groups and sharing. We shared the Margarita Pizza, Mediterranean Shrimp Salad, and vegetable soup.  Everything was delicious!  When I'm alone I always get the Portobello Spinach Panini or half-panini and soup of the day.  Staff are always friendly and helpful. Catering and meal prep plans available.
I loved everything  about it and the food is to die for.
First time here, my salad was so good, nice fresh ingredients,  very clean salad.  They were very friendly and helpful.
Keto and vegan friendly. Staff was friendly. Fast service
Looks modern and uninteresting from the outside, but the food is anything but! We had the gumbo, which is a creole type, and the shrimp bowl, and the turkey meatballs. WOW!! Delicious!
As a Gluten sensitive person this place was perfect. Lots of fresh options and the food was fabulous. Quick, clean and good! What more can you ask for, oh yeah reasonable prices too!

The food is tasteless. The staff even more disinterested. It is a shame because I do like the concept of walking in to grab what I need that day. I have tried multiple times to like them. This location is better than the others though.
Awesome
Very good healthy options, the food could taste better but it is a great place to have if you're trying to eat better.
People there are GREAT!!
Awesome healthier alternative compared to local fare.  Black bean burgers is tops.
Love the food here, and the service is great. Staff member Zac is amazing.

I would have rated 5 stars but my favorite place is cutting corners on quality. I have been going there since they opened. I have many food allergies and they were the go to people for me but now they are using a cheap olive oil or some other oil and I am having severe allergic reactions. And I really thought I found my favorite restaurant. If they don’t keep the old quality back up I will sadly have to part from them. The food is great but not the oils for me.
Delicious choices!!!
Healthy fast food at great prices. Food tastes great! 5 stars.
I LOVE THE ATMOSPHERE.  FRIENDLY SERVICE.  VERY HELPFUL CASHIER.  I WILL  DEFINITELY BE BACK.  DELICIOUS FOOD
Excellent, very impressed with this place. My first time, and will be back

so deliciously healthy! everything i've gotten here was AMAZING. the steak is cooked to perfection, the cauliflower mash is heavenly, and their pizza taste the same as what you would get anywhere else. the service is always super quick and ordering through apps like uber eats, you wait 15 minutes at most. would highly recommend!
Very good light healthy fare. I had half a chicken & provolone panini with bowl of butternut squash soup. Delicious. My husband had spinach and portobello mushroom panini with a side ceasar salad.
I'm partial to the Sonoma salad which is delicious. Other healthy options available as well.
This is my first time and I'm in love!!! Delicious Turkey Burger and salad. Good portions. I'm very happy and I'm not a huge fan of eating well. But this is good. And they have wine!!!!
Surprisingly yummy.
Wonderful upbeat environment and staff and even better food. Truly fresh and delicious. One of my favorite places.
Great healthy food
Gluten Free.
I wanted veggies. I made my salad. Everything was fresh. I got tuna as my protein. Quite tasty. I also got the sirloin. A little over done, but good flavor. Will be back.
Tasty, healthy food!

First visit here. I had the tomato basil soup to start.  I also had the Mediterranean shrimp bowl. VERY GOOD!  The kalamata olives and feta cheese gave this dish the perfect amount of salt. The roasted red peppers and cucumbers were really nice in the dish. I think I'll try the bbq shrimp and cauliflower grits next time, as the server let me taste a sample of the bbq sauce and found it tasty.

I am rarely impressed when it comes to healthy restaurants.  Most are over priced and the quantity of food makes me depressed.  Swegs was both well priced, and I left feeling quite satisfied!  Great crew, great food, and I have found a great new place to eat!
Great shrimp wrap. Light but filling.
Very Healthy Eating and tastes good too.
The food is fresh and the place is uneventful! Nice change from the usual.
SOOO GOOD!!!
Such a great spot for healthy, comfort food! Quick service & always with a smile.
Shat's low
Good food

Pros:  the place was very clean & the food came out fast Cons:  my steak was underseasoned & undercooked. I didn't have time to send it back so I just ate the veggies which seemed freshly cooked. Every else enjoyed their food, including my very picky niece & nephew.
This place was very good for a quick style restaurant. Not what I was expecting. The gumbo was better than 95% of the restaurants I have tried it at. That in itself is enough to give this a try.
Overall I really like SWEGS and it's great to have a healthy alternative available. I will say everything that I've tried there is great however I do wish the portions were a little bigger.
The food was fresh, flavorful and a healthy alternative compares to other fast foods in the area.  However, the portion is small.

Their healthy comfort food is great! I love the paninis and Mediterranean shrimp bowl. The shrimp and grits and turkey chilli are very spicy. There are options for vegan, dairy-free, heart-healthy,  etc.
Very clean place. The staff is energetic and friendly, but the food is over-priced for the mediocre taste.

I have eaten here several times and everything has always been very good. Until today....I went in with my boyfriend (because I had talked his ear off about how awesome everything was) and was disappointed for the first time. I ordered the stuffed bell peppers with the roasted zucchini, and the roasted sweet potatoes. Everything was great, except the sweet potatoes were seriously under cooked. We asked about them to see if they could be cooked for a little longer, and we're told thsts the way they were cooked. This makes me seriously sad. We were then offered something else to replace the potatoes, which we accepted.....but come on guys! 1. I was forced to throw away food that just needed a smig more cooking, which is wasteful. 2. Y'all are wasting money by replacing what I really wanted to another side. 3. The responce of, "well that's how they come" is a bit weak. With all this said, I will still eat here, but it makes me take a second before recommending it to others.
The BBQ Shrimp was too spicy and the interior was too corporate feeling. People were nice though.

I was craving for healthy good food. E found it at Swegs!!! I had the stuffed bell pepper with zucchini spaghetti and grilled tomatoes! Delicious! I also tried the sirloin with green beans and Brown rice. Very good. The price is fair.
Healthy food
Super clean and great quality food, but next time ask if how would people like their meat cooked.
Good clean meals.
Awful service. Could barely understand the woman taking my order and she rushed me off the phone. The online phone number doesn't work.
Delicious, healthy, and clean comfort food. This is definitely a place I'd go for having good tasty and green food.
Delicouse, healthy, quick, $10 for a full meal. My new staple :)
Good clean food and fast service
Tasty, healthy, quick food (not fast food, but food prepared quickly) with gluten-free and other dietary options.
Really tasty, healthy food! Great fast alternative option to fast food. Really friendly service, a little pricey but totally worth it. 5 stars, would definitely recommend!

Although the food is good, the portions sizes are extremely small. I ate in with my granddaughter and she order soup. There was hardly any in the bowl. I ordered two chilis to go and when I got home, the containers were not even half full. I complained about the soup and got a mumbled response that"that was the portion". I didnt look at the chili before I got home, but I should have. Did they run out and just charged me for what was left? My bill was 37.00 for what?  I did not have this at my first visit, but this one was awful. What is going on?
The food was really good and fresh tasting. A great alternative grab and go on my way home from work!

The staff was welcoming and helpful. And the food was even better.  Healthy food that doesn't taste like it at all. I've found my new daily lunch spot! Incredible food and service at an even better price. You really can't ask for more.
So glad they've opened another location. Went for opening day, and everything was great!!
